applicationInfo.name: Vehicle registration feature
applicationInfo.description:
**Notes:** _This is one of several examples demonstrating how you might use Threat Composer when working through AWS' Threat Modeling for Builders training. It is intentionally incomplete and is only used as a reference starting point. You may have different perspectives on the assumptions, threats and mitigations. This is OK, and could be used to start conversations with your team if you are taking the Threat Modeling Builders training as a group._

### System Summary

The vehicle registration feature is the decomposed portion of a fictitious AWS Connected Vehicle Solution. This feature aims to address the user story:

**“As a vehicle fleet manager, I want to register an existing IoT connected vehicle to bring it into service.”** 

This feature builds on top of features that have already been threat modeled and deployed - namely the web front end hosted on AWS Amplify and user authentication through Amazon Cognito.

architecture.description:
Our vehicle registration feature builds on top of features that have already been threat modeled and deployed - namely the web front end hosted on AWS Amplify and user authentication through Amazon Cognito.

### Included in the architecture

- The existing AWS Amplify deployment for the required static assets to render the webpage (HTML, JavaScript, and CSS); and
 - The existing Amazon Cognito integration for user pool authentication.

### API Information
The vehicle registration feature will support the following APIs configured in Amazon API Gateway and serviced from Lambda functions:

**ListVehicles**

- Returns information for all available IoT connected vehicles.
- No parameters are taken as inputs.
- Response includes `HTTP response code`, `vehicle_id` (STRING - GUID) and `vehicle_registered` (BOOLEAN).

**RegisterVehicle**

- Registers an existing IoT connected vehicle to bring it into service.
- Items including `vehicle_id` (STRING - GUID), `vehicle_type` (STRING), `vehicle_registration_number` (STRING) and PDF version of the vehicle registration document (Bytes) are taken as inputs.
- The existing DynamoDB table record is updated with vehicle_type and vehicle_registration_number. vehicle_registered is set to true.
- The vehicle registration document (PDF) is written as a blob of bytes to Amazon S3 (prefix: `\vehicle_registration_documents\.pdf`).
- Response includes `HTTP response code` and vehicle attributes, including `vehicle_id` (GUID), `vehicle_registered` (BOOLEAN)

**Deregister vehicle**

- Deregisters an existing registered IoT connected vehicle to bring out of service.
- `vehicle_id` (STRING - GUID) is taken as an input.
- The existing DynamoDB table record fields `vehicle_type` and `vehicle_registration_number` will be deleted, and `vehicle_registered` set to `false`.
- The vehicle registration document (PDF) will be deleted from Amazon S3 (prefix: `\vehicle_registration_documents\.pdf`).
- Response includes `HTTP response code` and vehicle attributes, including `vehicle_id` (GUID), `vehicle_registered` (BOOLEAN)

**DescribeVehicle**

- Returns information for a specific IoT connected vehicle - including pre-signed URL to the vehicle registration document (if registered).
- `vehicle_id` (STRING - GUID) is taken as an input.
- The existing DynamoDB table record will be queried, and the Lambda function code will generate a pre-signed URL  for vehicle registration document Amazon S3 object.
- Response includes `HTTP Response Code` and `vehicle attributes`, including `vehicle_id` (GUID), `vehicle_registered` (BOOLEAN), `vehicle_type` (STRING), `vehicle_registration_number` (STRING), `vehicle_registration_expiry_date` (STRING) and `vehicle_registration_document_url` (STRING)

dataflow.description: For simplicity, the reference data flow diagram solely covers the data/request plane of the vehicle registration feature and ignores the control/administrative plane . When threat modeling real systems, it is worthwhile to analyze all planes of operations, possibly using separate diagrams for each plane. The existing data flows of the frontend on AWS Amplify and authentication with Amazon Cognito are included for context, but are not specifically part of the exercises as they have been threat modeled prior to them being deployed.

assumptions.content: Our in-house code may have more security relevant bugs than up to date, industry-standard, open-source libraries.
We could improperly configure an AWS service and create unexpected risk.
Simple threats are more likely than complicated ones. For example, automated attacks originating from the internet are more likely than a chain of zero-day vulnerabilities.
AWS is responsible for protecting the infrastructure that runs services in the AWS Cloud. AWS provides services that we can use securely.
The security functionality and configuration options of individual AWS services can be relied upon.
We will focus on threats on the customer side of the AWS shared security model.

The Amazon API Gateway and AWS Lambda function are within the same trust zone.  The Lambda function trusts that requests originating from the API Gateway are already authenticated. Additional authentication is not performed by the Lambda function code.
RegisterVehicle: uploaded PDF documents are not being parsed by any custom code; the bytes are simply being written to S3.
The system design will align to the AWS Well-Architected Security Pillar.
We will encrypt our data-at-rest using DynamoDB and S3.
We encrypt our data-in-transit with strong Transport Layer Security (TLS).
There is a single DynamoDB table and single S3 bucket.
A single Lambda function is supporting all of the APIs.
We will use a single Lambda function for all of the APIs.
AWS services in this diagram are in the same region and same AWS account.
User web browsers are patched and up to date.
GUIDs can be treated as universally unique identifiers.
Every user will be authorized to call all APIs.
We will use REST-based APIs, processed by our API Gateway and Lambda.

metadata.value: This threat is a candidate for decomposition because it is fairly high level. What errors in authorization logic could occur? What threat actions could be performed?

threats.prerequisites: use an error in authorization logic
threats.threatImpact: the ability to perform actions they should not be authorized to perform
impactedAssets: vehicle registration, vehicle listing, registration status, and vehicle registration documents
threats.statement: A threat actor use an error in authorization logic can perform a threat action, which leads to the ability to perform actions they should not be authorized to perform, negatively impacting vehicle registration, vehicle listing, registration status, and vehicle registration documents

threats.prerequisites: with access to modify network traffic
threats.threatImpact: the API Gateway performing actions on another user's resources
impactedAssets: vehicle registration, vehicle listing, registration status, and vehicle registration documents
threats.statement: A threat actor with access to modify network traffic can manipulate API parameter input, which leads to the API Gateway performing actions on another user's resources, resulting in reduced integrity and/or confidentiality of vehicle registration, vehicle listing, registration status, and vehicle registration documents

threats.prerequisites: with access to an IAM Principal who can modify access to the S3 bucket
threats.threatAction: cause data in the Amazon S3 bucket to be deleted
threats.statement: A threat actor with access to an IAM Principal who can modify access to the S3 bucket can cause data in the Amazon S3 bucket to be deleted, resulting in reduced availability of vehicle registration documents

threats.prerequisites: with access to an IAM Principal who can modify access to the DynamoDB tables
impactedAssets: vehicle registration, vehicle listing, and registration status
threats.statement: A threat actor with access to an IAM Principal who can modify access to the DynamoDB tables can delete the data, resulting in reduced availability of vehicle registration, vehicle listing, and registration status

threats.prerequisites: who is able to access the AWS Lambda function logs
threats.threatAction: find sensitive data captured within the logs
impactedAssets: vehicle registration, vehicle listing, registration status, and vehicle registration documents
threats.statement: A threat actor who is able to access the AWS Lambda function logs can find sensitive data captured within the logs, resulting in reduced confidentiality of vehicle registration, vehicle listing, registration status, and vehicle registration documents

threats.prerequisites: who is authenticated and can make API requests
threats.threatAction: read information they should not be authorized to read
impactedAssets: vehicle registration, vehicle listing, registration status, and vehicle registration documents
threats.statement: A threat actor who is authenticated and can make API requests can read information they should not be authorized to read, resulting in reduced confidentiality of vehicle registration, vehicle listing, registration status, and vehicle registration documents

threats.threatAction: claim they did not do so
threats.threatImpact: the actor disputing financial charges related to the registration of a vehicle
threats.statement: A threat actor who can register a vehicle can claim they did not do so, which leads to the actor disputing financial charges related to the registration of a vehicle, resulting in reduced integrity of billing data

threats.prerequisites: with access to data in transit between the user and the Amazon S3 bucket
threats.statement: A threat actor with access to data in transit between the user and the Amazon S3 bucket can read or modify that data, resulting in reduced confidentiality and/or integrity of vehicle registration documents

threats.prerequisites: who is able to access the DynamoDB tables
impactedAssets: vehicle registration, vehicle listing, and registration status
threats.statement: A threat actor who is able to access the DynamoDB tables can access sensitive data, resulting in reduced confidentiality of vehicle registration, vehicle listing, and registration status

metadata.value: This threat is candidate to scope as 'Note Useful', as we may choose to rely on users correctly calling the right domain.

threats.prerequisites: with possession of a similar domain name
threats.threatAction: trick our users into interacting with a fake endpoint
impactedAssets: vehicle registration, vehicle listing, registration status, and vehicle registration documents
threats.statement: A threat actor with possession of a similar domain name can trick our users into interacting with a fake endpoint, which leads to interception of valid API requests, negatively impacting vehicle registration, vehicle listing, registration status, and vehicle registration documents
